As we will show in this section, measures on sigma algebras of binary set systems may be represented (and hence
visualized) by Jordan curves! (Jordan curves are simple closed curves in the plane.) We will define a condition which will ensure that the representation/visualization is unique. This visualization is guaranteed by several deep mathematical theorems.

Let $\tilde{\mathscr{D}}$ denote the binary set system of dyadic intervals
