$\Sigma\left(S^1,\tilde{\mathscr{D}}\right)$ (and vice versa). (The measures have the same product
coefficients.) We propose to visualize $\mu$ by visualizing the measure $\mu_{S^1}$. (The previous wind
examples shows that measures on sigma algebras generated by binary set systems can alternatively be
